pchoy wrote:
&gt;
&gt;
&gt; If I need to get FetchHTTP, I can do one of the following:
&gt;
&gt; ComplexType fetchHTTP = (ComplexType) (settingshandler.getModule
&gt; (&quot;HTTP&quot;));
&gt;
&gt; ComplexType fetchHTTP = (ComplexType)
&gt; (settingshandler.getComplexTypeByAbsoluteName
&gt; (settingshandler.getSettings(null), &quot;/crawl-order/fetch-
&gt; processors/HTTP&quot;));
&gt;
&gt; I think you can have other module with the same name &quot;HTTP&quot; right? So I
&gt; assume the second way is better?
&gt;











There can be only a single instance of any particular processor name in 
the settings system where name is the right-hand-side of the &#39;|&#39; in the 
src/conf/modules/processors.options file (&#39;HTTP&#39; in the above).   In 
other words, it is not possible to have 
&quot;/crawl-order/fetch-processors/HTTP&quot; and &quot;&quot;/crawl-order/writers/HTTP&quot; -- 
i.e. two processors of the same name but attached at different locations 
on the processing chain.

Given the above, just use your first single-line proposal for the 
getting of fetchHTTP.

Heads up: The above will all be vastly improved in the next Heritrix 
release when we move on to the new settings system (See the 
pjack_settings branch in Heritrix: 
https://archive-access.svn.sourceforge.net/svnroot/archive-crawler/branches/pjack_settings/).   
Stitching together processors in whatever combination you like -- or 
using a processor outside of a Heritrix context -- should be possible.

St.Ack



&gt;
&gt;  


